    <h2>{`Other tips for writing code on your Phone`}</h2>
    <p>{`While the GitHub app has no editor and is focused on triaging issues, pull requests, and other notifications; it does allow you to “share” to Working Copy if you have it installed, which has a fairly nice text editor built in. This doesn’t actually use Shortcuts specifically, but it does use a similar action in the share sheet within the GitHub app.`}</p>
